pdnPppBridgeExtMIB.name: pdnPppBridgeExtMIB
pdnPppBridgeExtMIB.organization: Paradyne Networks MIB Working Group Other information about group editing the MIB
pdnPppBridgeExtMIB.contactinfo: Paradyne Networks, Inc. 8545 126th Avenue North Largo, FL 33733 www.paradyne.com General Comments to: mibwg_team@paradyne.com Editor Clay Sikes
pdnPppBridgeExtMIB.description: The MIB module provides enterprise-specific extensions to the PPP-BRIDGE-MIB for managing the Bridge Control Protocol (BCP) on subnetwork interfaces that use the family of point-to-Point Protocols (PPP). BCP is a member of the Network Control Protocol suite of point-to-point protocols. The following documents should be referenced with respect to this MIB module: [RFC 1474] Kastenholz, F., `The Definitions of Managed Objects for the Bridge Network Control Protocol of the Point-to-Point Protocol', June 1993. [RFC 1661] Simpson, W., `The Point-to-Point Protocol', July 1994. [RFC 3518] Higashiyama, M., Baker, F., and Liao, T., `Point-to-Point Protocol (PPP) Bridging Control Protocol (BCP)', April 2003.

pdnPppBridgeExtTable.name: pdnPppBridgeExtTable
pdnPppBridgeExtTable.description: An entry in the PPP Bridge Table, pppBridgeTable. The PPP Bridge Table contains parameters and statistics for the local PPP entity.

pdnPppBridgeExtEntry.name: pdnPppBridgeExtEntry
pdnPppBridgeExtEntry.description: An entry in the Multilink PPP Configuration Table.

pdnPppBridgeBcpLinkStatusCurrState.name: pdnPppBridgeBcpLinkStatusCurrState
pdnPppBridgeBcpLinkStatusCurrState.description: The current state of the BCP State Machine.

pdnPppBridgeLocalToRemote802Tagged.name: pdnPppBridgeLocalToRemote802Tagged
pdnPppBridgeLocalToRemote802Tagged.description: Indicates whether or not the local PPP entity is transmitting IEEE 802 tagged frames. An enabled(1) indicates that frames will be transmitted 802 tagged. A disabled(2) indicate that frames will not be transmitted 802 tagged.

pdnPppBridgeRemoteToLocal802Tagged.name: pdnPppBridgeRemoteToLocal802Tagged
pdnPppBridgeRemoteToLocal802Tagged.description: Indicates whether or not the remote PPP entity is transmitting IEEE 802 tagged frames. An enabled(1) indicates that frames will be transmitted 802 tagged. A disabled(2) indicate that frames will not be transmitted 802 tagged.

pdnPppBridgeMediaConfigExtTable.name: pdnPppBridgeMediaConfigExtTable
pdnPppBridgeMediaConfigExtTable.description: An entry in the PPP Bridge Media Configuration Table, pppBridgeTable. The PPP Bridge Media Configuration Table contains objects relative to MAC media types.

pdnPppBridgeMediaConfigExtEntry.name: pdnPppBridgeMediaConfigExtEntry
pdnPppBridgeMediaConfigExtEntry.description: An entry in the Multilink PPP Media Configuration Table.

pdnPppBridgeMediaIeee802Tagged.name: pdnPppBridgeMediaIeee802Tagged
pdnPppBridgeMediaIeee802Tagged.description: Configures whether or not the local PPP entity will attempt to negotiate the IEEE-802-Tagged Frame option. An enabled(1) will result in the option being supported. A disabled(2) will result in the options not being supported.

pdnPppBridgeExtCompliance.name: pdnPppBridgeExtCompliance
pdnPppBridgeExtCompliance.description: The compliance statement for network elements implementing PPP Bridging Control Protocol.

pdnPppBridgeExtStateMachineGroup.name: pdnPppBridgeExtStateMachineGroup
pdnPppBridgeExtStateMachineGroup.description: Displays the BCP State Machine's state.

pdnPppBridgeExt802TaggedGroup.name: pdnPppBridgeExt802TaggedGroup
pdnPppBridgeExt802TaggedGroup.description: Displays whether or not IEEE 802 tagged frames are being transmitted.
